oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Conductor and others posed with train
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Tweetsie (East Tennessee and Western North Carolina Railroad train No. 11) stopped in the Doe River Gorge for photos. Crumley, the conductor, stands by four women and two men wearing overalls and hats. A man with hat off can be seen in the background.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
